snippet: The former Florida governor’s stands on immigration and education do not sit well with party members, some of whom say they are tired of the Bush name.
abstract: Presidential hopeful Jeb Bush prepares for first visit in three years to Iowa, where he faces indifference from many who remain unenthusiastic about notion of a political scion; Bush has had rapid success gaining support of party's establishment and elite donors, but has considerably less support among rank-and-file; polls indicate that more than one in four Republican caucusgoers say they would not support Bush.
lead_paragraph: The former Florida governor’s stands on immigration and education do not sit well with party members, some of whom say they are tired of the Bush name.

headline.main: Jeb Bush May Be One Bush Too Many for Rank-and-File Iowa G.O.P.
headline.print_headline: Jeb Bush May Be One Bush Too Many for Rank-and-File Iowa G.O.P.
